# GitHub Personal Access Token used at BUILD time to draw the per-repo
# "contributions per day" line graph on /github. Private repo activity is
# aggregated into a single blue "Private / other" line — no private repo
# names are exposed.
#
# IMPORTANT: to include PRIVATE contributions you must use a **classic** PAT:
#   https://github.com/settings/tokens  (Tokens (classic) → Generate new)
#   scopes: repo  +  read:user
# Fine-grained tokens return PUBLIC-ONLY data — the contribution total will
# exclude private work and the "Private / other" line will be empty.
#
# Local dev: copy this file to `.env` (already git-ignored) and fill it in.
# Cloudflare Pages: add GITHUB_TOKEN under Settings → Environment variables,
#   then trigger a new build. Without it, the page falls back to the heatmap.
GITHUB_TOKEN=
